                <head>450. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>The Antarctic Treaty was negotiated at the Conference on Antarctica held in
                    Washington October 15–December 1, 1959; it was signed by 18 nations on December
                    1, 1959. For documentation on the sessions of the Conference, see <ref
                        target="frus1958-60v02#pg_580">
                        <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1958–1960, volume II, pages
                        580</ref>–<ref target="frus1958-60v02#pg_632">632</ref>. For text of the
                    Treaty, see 12 <gloss target="#t_UST1">UST</gloss> 794 or <hi rend="italic"
                        >American Foreign Policy: Current Documents, 1961</hi>, pages 452–458. The
                    United States ratified the treaty on August 18, 1960, and it came into effect on
                    June 23, 1961, after ratification by all the signatories.</p>
            </div>
